The paper discusses the use of agent-based computer simulations to test hypotheses about collective human decision making, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper also mentions the use of evolutionary computation as a theoretical framework and research tool, which could fall under the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the collection of experimental data from human subjects, which could fall under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
